public abstract class DxSpace extends DxGeom implements DSpace
**************************************************************************** the base space class the contained geoms are divided into two kinds: clean and dirty. the clean geoms have not moved since they were put in the list, and their AABBs are valid. the dirty geoms have changed position, and their AABBs are may not be valid. the two types are distinguished by the GEOM_DIRTY flag. all dirty geoms come *before* all clean geoms in the list.

    • setSublevel

      public void setSublevel(int value)
      Description copied from interface: DSpace
      Sets sublevel value for a space.

      Sublevel affects how the space is handled in spaceCollide2 when it is collided with another space. If sublevels of both spaces match, the function iterates geometries of both spaces and collides them with each other. If sublevel of one space is greater than the sublevel of another one, only the geometries of the space with greater sublevel are iterated, another space is passed into collision callback as a geometry itself. By default all the spaces are assigned zero sublevel.

      NOTE: The space sublevel IS NOT automatically updated when one space is inserted into another or removed from one. It is a client's responsibility to update sublevel value if necessary.

      Specified by:
      setSublevel in interface DSpace
      Parameters:
      value - the sublevel value to be assigned
      See Also:
      • DSpace.getSublevel()
      • OdeHelper.spaceCollide2(DGeom, DGeom, Object, DNearCallback)

    • setManualCleanup

      public void setManualCleanup(int value)
      Description copied from interface: DSpace
      Sets manual cleanup flag for a space.

      Manual cleanup flag marks a space as eligible for manual thread data cleanup. This function should be called for every space object right after creation in case if ODE has been initialized with dInitFlagManualThreadCleanup flag.

      Failure to set manual cleanup flag for a space may lead to some resources remaining leaked until the program exit.

      Specified by:
      setManualCleanup in interface DSpace
      Parameters:
      value - 1 for manual cleanup mode and 0 for default cleanup mode
      See Also:
      • DSpace.setManualCleanup(int)
      • OdeHelper.initODE2(int)
